Lindiwe Nxumalo, 34, of Khula Village, Mtubatuba, was struck and killed by lightning on Sunday evening, Zululand Observer reports. The pregnant mother of four was apparently cooking on a gas stove when she was struck. READ MORE: Lightning strikes Jeep, sets house alight At the time, Nxumalo was with her 10-year-old and one-year-old daughters. The elder child also sustained minor injuries. She hid herself and her sister under the bed until the morning and reported the incident to a neighbour. &#8211; Caxton News Service